<div class="page">

  <div class="opening">
    <div class="opening-kicker">About</div>
    <div class="opening-statement">An operator built this,<br><strong>for operators.</strong></div>
    <p class="opening-sub">Kodiak Strategy isn't run by software people. It's run by someone who spent thirteen years on the floor of real businesses, making them run.</p>
  </div>

  <div class="section">
    <div class="section-label">The Founder</div>
    <div class="section-headline">Ryan Fagerstrom</div>
    <div class="founder-row">
      <div>
        <p>I spent thirteen years building and running owner-operated businesses, including two restaurants and a food truck. Hiring, scheduling, margins, logistics, the daily work of keeping an operation running. I know how a business actually works because I ran several of them.</p>
        <p>I'm not a technologist who decided to consult. I came up the same way most of my clients did, which means I know the difference between a tool that sounds impressive and one that actually removes work. That's the only kind of thing I'm interested in building.</p>
      </div>
      <div>
        <img src="/Ryan-family.jpeg" alt="Ryan Fagerstrom and family" class="founder-photo">
        <div class="photo-caption">Ryan Fagerstrom &middot; Founder</div>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="pull-quote">
      <p>You don't need to know everything about AI. You need someone who knows your operation.</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="section">
    <div class="section-label">Why Kodiak</div>
    <div class="section-headline">There was a gap.<br><em>Kodiak fills it.</em></div>
    <p>After my years as an operator, I spent serious time on how AI actually applies inside a real business. Not the hype. Where it genuinely saves time and money, and where it gets oversold by people who've never run anything.</p>
    <p>What I found was a clear gap. Business owners across South Dakota know AI matters, but they have no trusted local partner to tell them where it fits in their specific operation and then build it. National vendors sell generic tools. Big firms price themselves out of reach. Nobody is doing the practical, grounded version of this work for the businesses that need it.</p>
    <p><strong>That's what Kodiak does. We find where AI fits in your business, and we build it.</strong> We assess before we recommend, and we optimize a process before we automate it. It's how I'd have wanted to be treated as an owner, and it's the only way I'm willing to do this work.</p>
  </div>

  <div class="section">
    <div class="section-label">How We Work</div>
    <div class="section-headline">Four principles. <em>Every engagement.</em></div>
    <div class="values">
      <div class="value">
        <div class="value-title">Assessment first. Always.</div>
        <div class="value-desc">We never recommend a solution before we understand your operation. Every plan is built from your actual workflows, your team, and your goals. Never a template.</div>
      </div>
      <div class="value">
        <div class="value-title">Optimize before we automate.</div>
        <div class="value-desc">Automating a broken process just makes it faster. We fix the workflow first, then automate it, so the result runs on something worth running.</div>
      </div>
      <div class="value">
        <div class="value-title">Build things that get used.</div>
        <div class="value-desc">A tool that sits unused is a failure, however clever it is. We build what's practical, hand it off clean, and make sure it works the way your team works.</div>
      </div>
      <div class="value">
        <div class="value-title">Local, and accountable for it.</div>
        <div class="value-desc">Based in the Black Hills, working with businesses across South Dakota. Kodiak's reputation and mine are the same reputation, built in the same place.</div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="cta-section">
    <div class="cta-headline">Let's talk.</div>
    <p class="cta-sub">Twenty minutes about your operation and whether there's something here worth building. No pitch. No commitment beyond the call.</p>
